<main class="about-container">
  <h1>About</h1>

  <p>
    <strong>LitLog</strong> is your digital bookshelf for reflection, discovery, and contribution. It's a place where thoughtful readers turn books into lasting insights by logging their learning, reflections, and reviews. Whether you’re reading for growth, curiosity, or pure joy, LitLog helps you capture and share what truly matters from each page.
  </p>

  

  <section class="features">
    <h2>📘 What You Can Do on LitLog</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>🧠 <strong>Read and learn from others:</strong> Browse in-depth notes, summaries, and reviews by fellow readers — not just star ratings.</li>
      <li>✍️ <strong>Publish your own LitLogs:</strong> After finishing a book, write and share your reflections, lessons, and opinions in structured notes.</li>
      <li>⭐ <strong>Rate books meaningfully:</strong> Score books from 1 to 10 and explain your rating through your own lens.</li>
      <li>📅 <strong>Log your reading history:</strong> Track when you read a book, how it impacted you, and revisit it anytime.</li>
      <li>🧭 <strong>Discover impactful books:</strong> Find titles through other readers' notes, not algorithms. Choose your next read based on depth.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="why">
    <h2>💡 Why LitLog Exists</h2>
    <p>
      There are many platforms that let you rate or review books — but LitLog is different. Here, we care less about popularity and more about perspective. LitLog encourages readers to write notes that go beyond surface-level reactions. It’s a place to reflect on what a book meant to you and why.
    </p>
    <p>
      Your LitLog becomes a personal archive of your intellectual journey — a growing collection of takeaways, quotes, themes, and mental models from every book you’ve finished.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="community">
    <h2>🤝 A Community of Thinkers</h2>
    <p>
      LitLog is built for readers who love thinking deeply. Whether you’re into philosophy, psychology, sci-fi, or productivity — LitLog is your space to share what you’ve learned and explore what others have distilled.
    </p>
    <p>
      By publishing notes, you contribute to a growing knowledge base that helps others learn more effectively and choose books worth their time.
    </p>
  </section>

  <p class="closing">
    Start logging your reading journey today. <strong>LitLog</strong> — because every book deserves to be remembered.
  </p>
</main>

